<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-59-0113 </DOCNO><TEXT>This report is concerned with the use of tissue-equivalent phantoms indosimetry in order to solve some problems of radiological protection.Doses to 16 organs during diagnostic X-ray examinations of thorax andin urography were measured using a tissue-equivalent anthropomorphousphantom of a newborn baby elaborated and produced by the authors. Effectivedose equivalents and individual risk per patient have been calculated,too. An optimum construction of a protective shield a newborn duringurography has been established.</TEXT></DOC>